---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import ProseSection from '../../components/docs/ProseSection.astro';
import PhilosophyCallout from '../../components/docs/PhilosophyCallout.astro';
import ArtAsset from '../../components/docs/ArtAsset.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Art" description="Cleo logo and brand art assets">
  <div class="prose">
    <h1>Art</h1>
    <hr class="section-accent-rule" />
    <p class="page-lead">
      Logo and companion brand visuals. Flat planes, cool restraint, one amber accent — the same
      language as <a href="/foundations/illustration">illustration</a>, applied to identity.
    </p>
    <p>
      Use these assets on marketing surfaces, social, and documentation. Product UI continues to use
      the wordmark in Lora until vector lockups are finalized.
    </p>
  </div>

  <section class="art-section wide-band" aria-labelledby="logo-heading">
    <h2 id="logo-heading" class="art-section__title">Logo</h2>
    <ArtAsset
      title="Cleo wordmark"
      src="/art/logo-wordmark.png"
      alt="Cleo wordmark in midnight serif with amber dot above the letter o"
      filename="logo-wordmark.png"
      variant="logo"
      caption="Primary lockup. Humanist serif, e–o ligature, single amber dot. Display on color.page (#F5F3F0) or reversed on midnight with cream type when vectorized."
    />
  </section>

  <div class="prose">
    <ProseSection title="Logo usage">
      <ul>
        <li>One amber accent in the mark — do not add secondary warm colors in the same lockup</li>
        <li>Minimum clear space: height of the capital C on all sides</li>
        <li>Do not stretch, outline, or place on busy photography</li>
        <li>Favicon / app icon: simplify to C + dot; test at 32px before shipping</li>
      </ul>
    </ProseSection>
  </div>

  <section class="art-section wide-band" aria-labelledby="brand-art-heading">
    <h2 id="brand-art-heading" class="art-section__title">Brand art</h2>
    <p class="art-section__lead">
      Companion pieces for heroes, social, and empty states. Frame 8 energy — horizon, warmth, calm.
    </p>
    <div class="art-grid">
      <ArtAsset
        title="Horizon"
        src="/art/horizon.png"
        alt="Abstract horizon with amber sun on a navy and white divide, white wave form"
        filename="horizon.png"
        caption="Arrival and openness. Amber on the horizon line; cool navy sky. Use when the story is leaving the clinic on time."
      />
      <ArtAsset
        title="Reflection"
        src="/art/reflection.png"
        alt="Symmetrical organic form reflected across a horizon with amber semicircle at center"
        filename="reflection.png"
        caption="Balance and relief. Still water, single warm sun. Use for calm moments — completion, trust, peer recommendation."
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="prose">
    <ProseSection title="Color alignment">
      <p>When recreating or extending these assets, map to system tokens:</p>
      <table class="token-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Role</th><th>Token</th><th>Hex</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Dark fields</td><td><code>color.midnight</code></td><td>#0F1F30</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Structure</td><td><code>color.slate</code></td><td>#2E4057</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Light fields</td><td><code>color.page</code> / white planes</td><td>#F5F3F0</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Warm accent</td><td><code>color.amber</code></td><td>#D4841A</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </ProseSection>

    <PhilosophyCallout title="Distinct from product illustration">
      <p>
        Storyboard panels in the product stay organic and journey-focused. These brand marks are
        approved identity art — still flat and restrained, but allowed as logo companions on
        external surfaces.
      </p>
    </PhilosophyCallout>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  .art-section {
    margin: var(--space-section) 0;
  }

  .art-section__title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: var(--text-section);
    line-height: var(--leading-section);
    color: var(--color-midnight);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-6);
  }

  .art-section__lead {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-8);
    max-width: var(--content-max);
    color: var(--color-slate);
    line-height: var(--leading-body);
  }

  .art-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-8);
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .art-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
